{"entity": "Regulation (EU) 2016/679", "type": "content", "description": "Regulation (EU) 2016/679, commonly referred to as the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), is a pivotal legislative act established by the European Parliament and Council aimed at safeguarding personal data and ensuring the free movement of such data within the European Union (EU). This regulation lays down comprehensive rules for the processing of personal information, reflecting the importance of data protection and privacy in the digital age.

