{"entity": "Supervisory Authority", "type": "organization", "description": "The Supervisory Authority is an independent public agency established in each Member State to monitor and enforce compliance with data protection regulations. It plays a crucial role in ensuring that data processing activities adhere to applicable laws, thereby protecting individual privacy rights.

